    "architecture_notes": "WALKTHROUGH: The frontend lives in its own **container** (e.g., `frontend-webapp`). Inside this container the **presentation layer** holds all Angular components (≈287). The SASS compiler is part of the **infrastructure layer** – specifically the Angular build configuration (`angular.json`) that the Angular CLI (currently 18‑lts) invokes. The builder (`@angular-devkit/build-angular:application`) sits between the CLI and the Webpack bundler, orchestrating how SASS files are compiled into CSS. Neighboring pieces are:\n- **Presentation components** that import SASS files.\n- **Testing framework** (Karma + Playwright) that validates the rendered UI.\n- **CI pipeline** that runs `ng build` during the release process.\nChanging the builder therefore touches the build config (infrastructure), all style imports (presentation), and the CI workflow (operations). No backend containers or domain logic are directly affected.",
    "anticipated_questions": [
      {
        "question": "Do I need to modify the existing SASS files themselves?",
        "answer": "Only if they use the deprecated `@import` syntax. The migration guide (ADR) recommends converting those to the new `@use`/`@forward` syntax. Files that already use the new syntax can stay unchanged."
      },
      {
        "question": "Will this affect the current CI/CD pipeline?",
        "answer": "Yes. The pipeline installs the Angular CLI and runs the build. After switching to the new builder you must ensure the CI environment pulls the updated `@angular-devkit/build-angular` package and clears any cached build artifacts that reference the old compiler."
      },
      {
        "question": "What tests should I run after the migration?",
        "answer": "Run the full suite of frontend unit tests (Karma) and end‑to‑end tests (Playwright). Pay special attention to visual regression tests or any tests that assert CSS class presence, as style compilation changes can affect those."
      },
      {
        "question": "Is there any impact on the backend or other containers?",
        "answer": "No. The change is confined to the frontend container's build process and style assets. Backend services, domain logic, and data‑access layers remain untouched."
      },
      {
        "question": "What version of the new builder should I target?",
        "answer": "Use the version that ships with Angular 19 (the one referenced in the Angular 19 release notes). It will be compatible with the Angular CLI version that will be upgraded alongside this migration."
      }
